If he can't be better than this,
I just want to know.

728
00:43:50,545 --> 00:43:52,964
He's working this case right now.

729
00:43:54,508 --> 00:43:55,884
Serial killer, actually.

730
00:43:55,967 --> 00:44:00,430
You are not gonna try to tell me that this is
about a case. Try that shit on some civilian.

731
00:44:00,514 --> 00:44:03,809
Look, he'll get his head in a
certain place, he'll take a drink.

732
00:44:03,892 --> 00:44:05,852
I mean, a lot of us will.

733
00:44:05,936 --> 00:44:10,565
- It's more than just a drink he's taking.
- Beadie, I can't tell you what to do.

734
00:44:15,028 --> 00:44:17,030
I don't like giving up.

735
00:44:21,326 --> 00:44:24,538
Ok, I gotta go back to work.
Thanks for letting me vent.

736
00:44:32,754 --> 00:44:34,548
You want to get started today?

737
00:44:34,631 --> 00:44:37,259
- Sooner we decide on...
- After lunch, yeah.

738
00:45:25,724 --> 00:45:27,726
- Finally found a line, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

739
00:45:27,809 --> 00:45:30,520
Know that wasn't easy.
They been hidin' for years.

740
00:45:30,604 --> 00:45:33,064
- I'm a pro.
- Me, too.

741
00:45:34,149 --> 00:45:35,901
- Let me ask you...
- Hmm?

742
00:45:36,651 --> 00:45:38,278
When do the results come back?

743
00:45:39,487 --> 00:45:41,615
About an hour from this test.

744
00:45:41,698 --> 00:45:42,741
There you go.

745
00:45:42,824 --> 00:45:47,787
And they want you to believe
that there's only one side to this story,

746
00:45:47,871 --> 00:45:51,625
and that their so-called facts
cannot be denied.

747
00:45:51,708 --> 00:45:55,420
But we have some facts
of our own, don't we?

748
00:45:55,503 --> 00:45:56,546
Yeah!

749
00:45:56,630 --> 00:45:58,965
- We know who our leaders are.
- That's right.

750
00:45:59,049 --> 00:46:03,094
And we don't want them picking
our leaders for us, do we?

751
00:46:04,429 --> 00:46:08,433
And we will not stand idly by
as they single out our leaders

752
00:46:08,516 --> 00:46:10,602
and selectively prosecute,

753
00:46:10,685 --> 00:46:13,021
- or should I say persecute them...
- That's right!

754
00:46:13,104 --> 00:46:17,609
Just because they have the courage
and the fortitude to stand up for us.

755
00:46:20,070 --> 00:46:21,488
Let them hear you.

756
00:46:21,571 --> 00:46:24,324
Let them hear you loud and clear.

757
00:46:25,742 --> 00:46:29,287
Clay Davis isn't going anywhere, is he?

758
00:46:30,622 --> 00:46:33,708
- We need him, we're going to keep him...
- That's right!

759
00:46:33,792 --> 00:46:36,962
And damn anyone who says othennise.

760
00:46:37,045 --> 00:46:38,546
Clay Davis!

761
00:46:45,053 --> 00:46:48,390
What the fuck is this I hear about
you might not stand tall on this?

762
00:46:48,473 --> 00:46:51,267
You got that wrong, old friend.
I'm gonna carry this.

763
00:46:51,351 --> 00:46:53,812
You damn sure better. Because if you don't,

764
00:46:53,895 --> 00:46:57,315
you won't be able to squeeze another
greenback out of this town

765
00:46:57,399 --> 00:46:59,651
for the rest of your natural life.

766
00:46:59,734 --> 00:47:03,989
We shall not be,
we shall not be moved

767
00:47:04,072 --> 00:47:08,326
We shall not be,
we shall not be moved...

768
00:47:08,660 --> 00:47:09,995
Ooh, la, la!

769
00:47:10,078 --> 00:47:11,788
Lookie here.

770
00:47:11,871 --> 00:47:14,499
- The fuck is that?
- A change of pace.

771
00:47:15,375 --> 00:47:18,253
They look kinda hot with their clothes on.

772
00:47:21,006 --> 00:47:23,758
Hey, Clarice.

773
00:47:23,842 --> 00:47:26,344
Your serial killer called
the Baltimore sun.

774
00:47:26,428 --> 00:47:29,180
Some goof claiming to be your guy
called a reporter.

775
00:47:29,264 --> 00:47:32,017
- One of the guys writing this shit up.
- Gotta be a crank call.

776
00:47:32,100 --> 00:47:33,435
Probably so.

777
00:47:33,518 --> 00:47:35,562
But seeing as it's the fucking newspaper

778
00:47:35,645 --> 00:47:39,607
you go over there and
you set them straight.

779
00:47:56,624 --> 00:47:57,917
Go ahead.

780
00:48:07,177 --> 00:48:08,470
Negative.

781
00:48:11,890 --> 00:48:14,392
- Negative means...
- I know what it means.

782
00:48:16,436 --> 00:48:18,772
- Must be wrong.
- It ain't wrong.

783
00:48:18,855 --> 00:48:21,232
All the shit I done.

784
00:48:21,316 --> 00:48:22,901
All the works I shared.

785
00:48:22,984 --> 00:48:26,237
My best boy years back? I fired
off the same hypo as him dozens of times.

786
00:48:26,321 --> 00:48:28,323
He had the bug for sure.

787
00:48:30,158 --> 00:48:32,285
That shit ain't right nohow, man.

788
00:48:33,995 --> 00:48:36,247
You're disappointed.

789
00:48:36,331 --> 00:48:38,208
Shit, this ain't about the bug, is it?

790
00:48:38,291 --> 00:48:42,212
This is you tryin' to make
the past be everything, mean everything.

791
00:48:42,295 --> 00:48:45,423
You don't even wanna think
about the here and now.

792
00:48:45,507 --> 00:48:47,467
Sorry, bubs.

793
00:48:47,550 --> 00:48:50,011
Shame ain't worth as much as you think.

794
00:48:51,262 --> 00:48:52,347
Let it go.

795
00:48:56,810 --> 00:49:00,438
He said he wanted people to know
there'd be 12 bodies before he's finished.

796
00:49:00,522 --> 00:49:03,525
He said, quote, "I came to take 12."

797
00:49:03,608 --> 00:49:05,652
I said, "what happens after 12?"

798
00:49:05,735 --> 00:49:08,947
He said, quote,
"I go somewhere else," unquote.

799
00:49:09,030 --> 00:49:13,743
I asked him about the bite marks. He said that
they wanted him to bite, they asked for that.

800
00:49:13,827 --> 00:49:17,622
He complained that the article
made him sound like a pervert.

801
00:49:17,705 --> 00:49:20,416
I asked him if he was angry at the men.

802
00:49:20,500 --> 00:49:21,500
He hung up.

803
00:49:21,543 --> 00:49:24,963
He called you on your cellphone?
Why didn't he call the paper?

804
00:49:25,046 --> 00:49:29,217
I was all over the city yesterday
handing my cards out to homeless men.

805
00:49:29,300 --> 00:49:32,011
He probably got the number from a card.

806
00:49:32,095 --> 00:49:33,721
Shit, I might've handed him a card.

807
00:49:33,805 --> 00:49:37,100
I think this is the guy.
I mean, a chill ran down my back.

808
00:49:37,183 --> 00:49:39,644
But there's no way to know.
I mean, if it's some other nut,

809
00:49:39,727 --> 00:49:41,813
we're gonna look like
fools if we print this.

810
00:49:41,896 --> 00:49:44,190
Your cellphone caught the number?
He dialed you.

811
00:49:44,274 --> 00:49:45,441
Yeah, I dialed it back.

812
00:49:45,525 --> 00:49:48,403
Payphone on south Hanover
near west street.

813
00:49:52,907 --> 00:49:54,635
- What did he sound like?
- What do you mean?

814
00:49:54,659 --> 00:49:56,035
You talk to people for a living.

815
00:49:56,119 --> 00:49:58,246
Did he sound black, white? Younger, older?

816
00:49:58,329 --> 00:49:59,664
High-pitched voice or low?

817
00:49:59,747 --> 00:50:02,375
Uh, he sounded, to me, like a white guy.

818
00:50:02,458 --> 00:50:05,920
Not a deep voice, but
calm, almost monotone.

819
00:50:06,838 --> 00:50:11,092
He sounded older, I would say, 40s.
Not a real young guy.

820
00:50:11,176 --> 00:50:13,761
- Can I have your notebook?
- You can't have his notes.

821
00:50:13,845 --> 00:50:17,390
As this isn't a confidential source,
we won't invoke the Maryland shield law,

822
00:50:17,473 --> 00:50:19,517
but he'll type up a copy for you.

823
00:50:19,601 --> 00:50:22,353
But the actual document is
property of the Baltimore sun.

824
00:50:22,437 --> 00:50:25,106
So type it up, like, now.

825
00:50:25,190 --> 00:50:27,525
So, you're saying this could be the killer?

826
00:50:28,109 --> 00:50:29,611
Can we talk off the record?

827
00:50:31,237 --> 00:50:34,032
The homicide unit
received a phone call this morning

828
00:50:34,115 --> 00:50:36,367
from a payphone
from the same neighborhood,

829
00:50:36,451 --> 00:50:40,788
and based on Scott's voice description,
and the use of the number 12...

830
00:50:42,207 --> 00:50:45,376
Let's just say we need to find
whoever it was made both those calls.

831
00:50:45,460 --> 00:50:47,045
He made another call?

832
00:50:47,128 --> 00:50:51,799
Detective, as a newsman, I'm inclined
to include these details in our coverage

833
00:50:51,883 --> 00:50:55,386
if there's a credible chance the
killer was in contact with our reporter.

834
00:50:55,470 --> 00:50:58,097
Would doing so have any negative effect
on your investigation?

835
00:50:58,181 --> 00:51:01,851
Actually, these calls are
our best means of finding this guy.

836
00:51:01,935 --> 00:51:05,230
Every call he makes, every word he says,
to you and to us,

837
00:51:05,313 --> 00:51:06,981
can only provide information.

838
00:51:07,774 --> 00:51:10,777
- If we do run a story...
- You can't say he's contacted police.

839
00:51:10,860 --> 00:51:13,571
You can't print that part of it
under any circumstances.

840
00:51:13,655 --> 00:51:16,741
Ok, then how do we characterize
what the police think

841
00:51:16,824 --> 00:51:20,036
- about this call to Scott?
- You can say that we're, uh...

842
00:51:20,119 --> 00:51:21,496
Taking it seriously.

843
00:51:22,121 --> 00:51:25,792
Going fonnard, is it possible
that you would Grant a one-party consent

844
00:51:25,875 --> 00:51:29,712
for us to monitor your reporter's cellphone
and office phones?

845
00:51:29,796 --> 00:51:31,673
- Absolutely not.
- I'm sorry, detective,

846
00:51:31,756 --> 00:51:33,716
but our ability to report is dependent upon

847
00:51:33,800 --> 00:51:37,011
our maintaining the confidentiality
of our conversations.

848
00:51:37,804 --> 00:51:41,933
We're perfectly willing to share with you
the information this individual has

849
00:51:42,016 --> 00:51:44,018
as he's definitely not
a confidential source.

850
00:51:44,102 --> 00:51:46,580
But we're not going to consent
to the Baltimore police department

851
00:51:46,604 --> 00:51:48,314
monitoring our phones.

852
00:51:48,398 --> 00:51:51,192
- You'll tap the payphone, I guess.
- Don't print that, either.

853
00:51:51,276 --> 00:51:54,487
Don't print anything
about where the killer calls from.

854
00:51:54,570 --> 00:51:55,655
He'll change up.

855
00:51:58,116 --> 00:52:00,785
Well, I'll type up my notes quick.

856
00:52:00,868 --> 00:52:04,247
- Big story for you guys, huh?
- Well, ten minutes ago I'd've said

857
00:52:04,330 --> 00:52:06,124
this whole thing was complete bullshit.

858
00:52:06,207 --> 00:52:08,167
Shows what I know, I guess.

859
00:52:21,514 --> 00:52:23,641
Which is why I'm gonna
fight this thing.

860
00:52:23,725 --> 00:52:27,478
I am innocent and I have done
nothing except serve the people.

861
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:28,980
Oh, I believe you, senator.

862
00:52:29,063 --> 00:52:32,900
I've seen the good work
you've done for the community...

863
00:52:44,370 --> 00:52:46,331
That's Eddie cantor, right?

864
00:52:49,083 --> 00:52:50,793
It's perfect.

865
00:52:50,877 --> 00:52:54,088
- Mcnulty, it's perfect.
- I couldn't believe it.

866
00:52:54,172 --> 00:52:56,883
I'm sitting there,
all this bullshit coming at me,

867
00:52:56,966 --> 00:52:59,010
thinking, Christ, this is a waste of time.

868
00:52:59,093 --> 00:53:03,014
Then I realized - this is the wiretap.
Right here. They're giving it to me.

869
00:53:03,097 --> 00:53:04,807
Never mind me making a crank call.

870
00:53:04,891 --> 00:53:07,769
This right here is Lester freamon's
motherfucking wire.

871
00:53:17,570 --> 00:53:19,530
What if they check this?

872
00:53:19,614 --> 00:53:23,326
How many guys in this unit
have ever hooked up a wiretap?

873
00:53:23,409 --> 00:53:26,454
They don't know which wire goes where.

874
00:53:27,288 --> 00:53:28,706
Explain it to me again,

875
00:53:28,790 --> 00:53:32,043
because I think I'm a smart guy,
but this shit makes my head hurt.

876
00:53:32,126 --> 00:53:34,545
They think they're up on
your killer's cellphone,

877
00:53:34,629 --> 00:53:38,216
but they'll never catch a call
because this goes nowhere.

878
00:53:38,299 --> 00:53:41,677
And meanwhile,
using the same court authorization,

879
00:53:41,761 --> 00:53:45,556
I'm on the live wire down at the
detail office, listening to Mario.

880
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:48,893
Every day, you file
office and court reports

881
00:53:48,976 --> 00:53:51,896
saying there's been no further
contact with the serial killer.

882
00:53:51,979 --> 00:53:56,234
I file exactly nothing, but use what I hear

883
00:53:56,317 --> 00:53:58,820
to rig the case on our real target.

884
00:53:58,903 --> 00:54:00,405
And when it goes to court...

885
00:54:00,488 --> 00:54:02,615
No mention of a wiretap.
It's all based on a cl.

886
00:54:02,698 --> 00:54:03,699
There it is.

887
00:54:03,783 --> 00:54:06,661
Four copies signed by the judge.

888
00:54:06,744 --> 00:54:10,415
Emergency order for
telephonic intercept of a cellphone,

889
00:54:10,498 --> 00:54:14,001
number 410-915-0909.

890
00:54:14,085 --> 00:54:17,755
- If the machine is rigged, you're good to go.
- You're up.

891
00:54:17,839 --> 00:54:19,149
- Good hunting.
- Howie?

892
00:54:19,173 --> 00:54:22,051
- Yo.
- You got midnight shift.

893
00:54:22,135 --> 00:54:24,220
Worden'll be in to relieve you at six.

894
00:54:24,303 --> 00:54:28,099
After worden, my squad will pick up
monitoring on the dayshift.

895
00:54:32,854 --> 00:54:34,605
Excuse me.

896
00:54:34,689 --> 00:54:38,443
Don't look so pissy.
We're actually paying overtime for this.

897
00:55:40,713 --> 00:55:41,714
O-dog!

898
00:55:43,758 --> 00:55:45,134
My leg!

899
00:55:45,218 --> 00:55:46,886
Stay the fuck down!

900
00:56:32,014 --> 00:56:33,015
What the...

901
00:56:38,354 --> 00:56:39,355
Damn.

902
00:57:15,683 --> 00:57:17,268
What the...

